<TEXT>
<P>
Contel Cellular Inc.: The Atlanta-based cellular phone services provider said 
it had a second-quarter loss of $29.3 million, contrasted with a $1.1-million 
profit in the year-ago period. The company said the loss was related to the 
acquisition in February of 13 cellular systems from McCaw Cellular 
Communications. The acquisitions tripled Contel's quarterly revenue -- to $44 
million. 
