<TEXT>
<P>
Varian Associates Inc.: The Palo Alto-based computer, instruments and 
electronics company reported a third-quarter loss of $34.1 million, contrasted 
with a profit of $9 million a year ago. Sales were up 13% to $344 million. 
Varian, which is reorganizing, said the loss was the result of $31.9 million in 
restructuring charges and $15.2 million in charges for discontinuing some 
operations. 
