</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beckman Instruments Inc.: The Fullerton-based producer of automated systems and 
supplies used in biological laboratories said second-quarter net income fell 
25% to $8.6 million, while revenue rose 1% to $202.9 million. Research and 
development funding in the quarter rose 21%, Beckman said, and this investment 
in new products reduced earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
