School District's downtown headquarters to welcome the district's new 
superintendent. William R. Anton said he will give up the bodyguard-driver and 
send him to be a security officer "for a school that needs it most." ; Photo, 
Supt. William R. Anton appears at his first press conference as head of the Los 
Angeles school district. LARRY BESSEL / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
