<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
MOLESTATION SUSPECT SLAIN IN MEXICAN JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ventura man jailed on child sexual assault charges was found stabbed to death 
in his cell at La Loma prison in Nuevo Laredo, Mexico, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Federal judicial police say William Lee Heigel's body was discovered early 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Raul Villegas, group leader for the State Judicial Police, said a preliminary 
inquest indicated that Heigel died of multiple stab wounds to the neck, 
shoulders, back and chest. 
</P>
<P>
Villegas said Heigel was attacked with a machete by a man sharing the cell. The 
suspect was identified as Cresencio Hernandez Tovar, 35. 
</P>
<P>
Heigel, 43, was a convicted sex offender who was first arrested for molesting 
boys in 1965. Officials said he had an IQ of 60. He spent much of his life in 
California mental institutions and later in prisons for sex crimes. 
</P>
<P>
Mario Trejo Constantino, head of Nuevo Laredo Ministerio Publico, said Tovar 
told investigators that he had been sleeping when Heigel started kicking him 
and a fight ensued. Officials don't know how Tovar got the knife, Trejo 
Constantino said. 
</P>
<P>
Tovar is serving a 22-year sentence for several offenses, including aggravated 
sexual assault and robbery. 
</P>
<P>
Heigel came to the attention of Mexican authorities several months ago in 
connection with a series of sexual assaults on young boys in different cities. 
He was arrested April 30 in Nuevo Laredo as he stepped off a bus from Mexico 
City. 
</P>
<P>
He was detained by police after they discovered pornographic photos of boys in 
his luggage. A federal judge in Nuevo Laredo ordered Heigel held for medical 
observation at La Loma. 
</P>
<P>
Trejo Constantino said Heigel admitted to having molested as many as 50 boys 
under the age of 12 over three years. THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 
</P>
</TEXT>
