<HEADLINE>
<P>
MT. CARMEL HIGH NAMES THREE COACHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mt. Carmel High Athletic Director Frank Andruski announced the hiring of three 
coaches Monday. The vacancies were created by the departure of several Mt. 
</P>
<P>
Carmel coaches for Rancho Bernardo High, which opens this fall. 
</P>
<P>
Andruski named Mike Martino as the water polo coach, Tracey Johnson as the 
girls basketball coach and Paul Robinson as the boys tennis coach. 
</P>
<P>
Martino was an assistant water polo coach last year at Mt. Carmel and worked 
with the freshman and junior varsity from 1986 to 1989. A Mt. Carmel graduate, 
Martino was also the swimming coach at Kearney High. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who played at Mesa College in 1981 and 1982, was a varsity assistant 
to former Mt. Carmel coach Peggy Brose for the past four seasons. Brose left to 
coach girls basketball at Rancho Bernardo. 
</P>
<P>
During those years, Mt. Carmel won Section titles in 1988 and 1990. During her 
high school athletic career, Johnson was selected athlete of the year at Poway 
in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson will remain as the girls tennis coach and will replace Tony Goffredo 
as the boys coach. 
</P>
<P>
Andruski said he has yet to name a baseball, softball, gymnastics and swimming 
coach. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072490-0078 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 251681 </DOCID>
