REGIONAL EARNINGS: 3-D SYSTEMS EXPECTS TURNAROUND IN 2ND PERIOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
3-D Systems Inc., the Canadian parent of a Valencia company with the same name, 
said it expects to report a profit of between $100,000 and $200,000 when its 
final figures for the second quarter that ended June 30 are released at the end 
of this month. 
</P>
<P>
3-D Systems, which manufactures machines that make three-dimensional plastic 
models or prototypes of objects by using computer-aided designs and lasers, 
lost $984,736 in the second quarter of 1989. Sales in the latest period nearly 
doubled, to $7.1 million from $3.7 million, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
3-D Systems attributed the turnaround in the latest quarter to cost-cutting, 
including layoffs, and to additional marketing efforts. 
</P>
