<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
2 SHARE LOTTO'S $30-MILLION PRIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two ticket-holders -- one from San Francisco and the other from Los Angeles -- 
shared the $30,120,000 grand prize in the weekend "Lotto 6-53" drawing, 
according to state lottery officials. 
</P>
<P>
Cecelia Gaddini, 66, a retired city worker from the Bay Area, said she was 
"still in shock" and doesn't know what she will do with 20 annual checks of 
$602,400 each, after taxes. The Los Angeles winner was not immediately 
identified. Fourteen tickets contained five of six winning numbers, plus the 
bonus number, each winning its owner $66,582, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
