<TEXT>
<P>
Mark Gastineau, former New York Jet defensive end, has been placed on waivers 
by the British Columbia Lions of the Canadian Football League. 
</P>
<P>
Under CFL rules, if the 33-year-old Gastineau clears waivers, the Lions could 
place him on their practice roster. Because of Gastineau's large personal 
services contract with Lion Owner Murray Pezim, it's unlikely that another CFL 
team would claim him. 
</P>
