<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: CELTICS HIRE CASEY AS ASSISTANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don Casey, fired as coach of the Clippers after last season, was hired Monday 
as an assistant by the Boston Celtics. 
</P>
<P>
Casey joins the staff of Chris Ford, a former Celtic assistant who was named 
coach after Jimmy Rodgers was fired following the season. 
</P>
<P>
Casey, 53, replaced Gene Shue as the Clippers' coach on Jan. 19, 1989, and 
served until the end of last season. The Clippers were 41-85 under Casey, 
including 30-52 last season, when they finished sixth in the Pacific Division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
