<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL TO CONSIDER STADIUM PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Stadium Business Park, an 18-acre office and retail center, will be the 
latest addition to the growing business community around Anaheim Stadium if the 
City Council approves the project tonight. 
</P>
<P>
The project will include four high-rise office towers (two with 20 stories and 
two with 16 stories), a 400-room hotel, a health club, an eight-story parking 
structure and various restaurants and retail shops. 
</P>
<P>
Though the $500-million development deal is nearly complete, planners have not 
yet disclosed possible tenants for the project, said Steven Dietrich, a 
consultant for the proposal. 
</P>
<P>
Stadium Business Park is planned for a rectangular plot across the street from 
the main entrance of Anaheim Stadium on State College Boulevard just south of 
Katella Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Dietrich said developers were attracted to the area because of its freeway 
access, its proximity to the forthcoming Anaheim Arena and the expanding 
Anaheim Convention Center. 
</P>
<P>
If approved tonight, groundbreaking for the project is scheduled to begin in 
three to five years but could start sooner depending on the progress of the 
arena and other nearby projects, he said. LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ANAHEIM (CA) -- DEVELOPMENT AND REDEVELOPMENT; BUSINESS PARKS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
