<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOOVER NAMED BASEBALL ASSISTANT AT UCI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fred Hoover, an assistant baseball coach at Cal State Fullerton, has been named 
assistant baseball coach at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Hoover, 59, will work primarily with pitchers at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Hoover had been an assistant coach at Fullerton for the past two seasons. 
Before that, he was head baseball coach at Golden West College for 22 years, 
compiling a 478-269 record. At Golden West, his teams won seven conference 
titles and finished second seven times. 
</P>
<P>
At Irvine, Hoover replaces Robin Dreizler, who recently accepted a position 
with UCLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
