<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The nation's Big Three auto makers today said sales of their North 
American-made cars and light trucks tumbled 15.9% in mid-July compared with 
last year, when the sales rate zoomed upward. 
</P>
<P>
Auto makers, analysts and dealers had been watching the numbers closely to see 
if a generally upward trend in the sales rate during the last two reporting 
periods would continue. 
</P>
<P>
But General Motors Corp., Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. said car sales fell 
17.8% and truck sales dropped 13%. 
