<TEXT>
<P>
A watch given to Redd Foxx by the late Elvis Presley brought $17,500 Monday in 
an IRS auction to help pay the comedian's back taxes. 
</P>
<P>
The watch was sold along with about 70 other pieces of jewelry and other items 
owned by Foxx in an auction that brought in about $34,000. 
</P>
<P>
The auction followed a May auction of eight vehicles belonging to Foxx that 
brought the IRS about $49,000. 
</P>
<P>
Foxx didn't attend Monday's auction, but his attorney, Marc Risman, said he 
would be disappointed that the Presley watch brought in so little. 
