<HEADLINE>
<P>
2ND PART OF 'LOVE AND HATE' SCORES HIGH FOR NBC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A cagey bit of programming worked for NBC in the weekly television ratings, 
with the conclusion of a two-part movie grabbing the top slot this week and 
Part 1 scoring high the last time around, it was reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Monday night's broadcast of Part 2 of "Love and Hate: A Marriage Made in Hell," 
starring Kate Nelligan, was the top-rated show in the weekly Nielsen ratings 
for the week of July 16-22. 
</P>
<P>
Part 1 of the miniseries, broadcast July 15, placed sixth in the ratings for 
the week of July 9-15. The show's ratings were the third-highest for all NBC 
miniseries broadcast this season, following "Blind Faith" and "Drug Wars: The 
Camarena Story." 
</P>
<P>
In other good news for NBC, the July 17 special "Real Life with Jane Pauley" 
tied for fifth place, the highest-ever rating for a network news special. Five 
"Real Life" specials have been scheduled for the summer. 
</P>
<P>
Reruns of the perennially top-rated "Cheers" (NBC) and "Roseanne" (ABC) were in 
second and third place respectively and ABC's "20/20" zipped to fourth place, 
compared with its 21st place showing a week ago. 
</P>
<P>
It was a three-way pileup in seventh place, with Fox's "The Simpsons" and 
"Married . . . With Children" tying with NBC's "Golden Girls." 
</P>
<P>
"The Miss Teen USA" pageant broadcast on CBS rounded out the top 10. Some usual 
top 10 finishers, CBS's "60 Minutes" and NBC's "The Cosby Show" and "A 
Different World," were bumped to 11th, 12th and 13th places respectively. 
</P>
<P>
A rerun of NBC's "Quantum Leap" outpaced two original shows in the prime-time 
race July 18, placing 39th over ABC's Barbara Walters special "The Perfect 
Baby" (41st place) and CBS's "Top Cops" in 43rd place. 
</P>
<P>
NBC won five nights of the week -- Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday and 
Saturday -- its first such showing since Feb. 26. ABC won Friday night and 
Sunday belonged to CBS. 
</P>
<P>
For the week ending July 22, it was the 10th consecutive win for NBC with a 
10.2 rating and a 20 share, followed by CBS with an 8.7 rating and a 17 share. 
ABC had an 8.4 rating and a 16 share and Fox posted a 6.1 rating and a 12 
share. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
TOP 10 SHOWS 
</P>
<P>
The top programs for the week ending Sunday, July 22, according to the A. C. 
Nielsen Co., were: 
</P>
<P>
1. NBC Monday Movie: Love and Hate (NBC) 
</P>
<P>
2. Cheers (NBC) 
</P>
<P>
3. Roseanne (ABC) 
</P>
<P>
4. 20/20 (ABC) 
</P>
<P>
5. Empty Nest (NBC) 
</P>
<P>
(tie) Real Life-Jane Pauley (NBC) 
</P>
<P>
7. Golden Girls (NBC) 
</P>
<P>
(tie) Married With Children (Fox) 
</P>
<P>
(tie) The Simpsons (Fox) 
</P>
<P>
10. Teen USA Pageant (CBS) 
</P>
</TEXT>
