<P>
GENE SHUE NAMED GM OF 76ERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gene Shue, the fourth-winningest coach in NBA history and a former coach of the 
76ers, was named the Philadelphia team's general manager today. 
</P>
<P>
Shue's teams won 784 games in his 23 seasons as an NBA head coach at 
Washington, Philadelphia and San Diego. He, Bill Fitch, Don Nelson and Cotton 
Fitsimmons are the only coaches in league history named coach of the year 
twice. 
</P>
<P>
Shue succeeds John Nash, who resigned at the end of last season and is now 
general manager of the Washington Bullets. 
